⚙️ Step 3 — Re-instantiate inside QRAE

Now we build actual levers.

⸻

1. 🧬 Freshness Engine (Monotonic layer)

Core idea:
Track how “old” an opportunity is.

Signal:

freshness = now_monotonic - first_seen_time

Use it to:
	•	Prioritize new listings (higher edge)
	•	Devalue stale arbitrage opportunities
	•	Detect slow-moving inventory

Action rule:

New = alpha
Old = risk

⸻

2. 🔄 Cycle Alignment Engine (Standard layer)

Core idea:
Markets move in rhythms.

Signals:
	•	Time of day
	•	Day of week
	•	Seasonal events

Use it to:
	•	Buy during low demand windows
	•	Sell into high demand cycles

Example:
	•	Fitness gear spikes in January
	•	Toys spike in December
	•	Energy products spike pre-summer

Action rule:

Don’t just find deals—time them into demand

⸻

3. ⚡ Urgency Amplifier (Perceived layer)

Core idea:
Perception changes conversion speed.

Signals:
	•	Scarcity
	•	Movement speed
	•	Listing freshness (visual)

Use it to:
	•	Price slightly below market for velocity
	•	Use listing timing (new = more attention)
	•	Bundle items to create “newness”

Action rule:

Faster turnover > max margin (most of the time)

⸻

🧩 Step 4 — Combine into a single scoring system

Now we fuse all three layers.

🧮 QRAE Time-Aware Score

score = (freshness_weight * freshness_score)
      + (cycle_weight * demand_alignment)
      + (urgency_weight * velocity_potential)


